        "body": "**Describe the bug**\nThe dropdown menu for toggling UI elements (Menubar, Sidebar, Issues, Fullscreen) opens correctly when clicked.\nHowever, clicking the same toggle button again does not close the dropdown.\nThe only way to close it is by clicking somewhere else on the page.\nThis breaks expected toggle behavior and affects usability.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n\n1. Open DrawDB.\n2. Click the UI toggle dropdown button (the one with the two horizontal rectangles icon).\n3. Observe the dropdown opening.\n4. Click the same button again.\n5. The dropdown does not close.\n\n**Expected behavior**\nThe dropdown should function as a toggle:\n\n- First click → open\n- Second click → close\nInstead, it stays open until the user clicks outside the dropdown.\n\n\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\n - OS: macOS\n - Browser: Chrome",
